```matlab
% Define the size of the cube
sideLength = 1;

% Create the coordinates for the vertices of the cube
vertices = [0 0 0; sideLength 0 0; sideLength sideLength 0; 0 sideLength 0;...
            0 0 sideLength; sideLength 0 sideLength; sideLength sideLength sideLength; 0 sideLength sideLength];

% Create the connections between the vertices to form the faces of the cube
faces = [1 2 3 4; 2 6 7 3; 6 5 8 7; 5 1 4 8; 4 3 7 8; 5 6 2 1];

% Plot the cube
patch('Vertices',vertices,'Faces',faces,'FaceColor','g','FaceAlpha',0.5);

% Adjust plot appearance
axis equal;
xlabel('X');
ylabel('Y');
zlabel('Z');
title('3D Cube');
```

This code snippet uses the `patch` function in MATLAB to define the vertices and faces of the cube and then plots it in a 3D figure. Adjust the `sideLength` variable to change the size of the cube according to your preferences. The `'FaceColor'` option sets the color of the cube, and `'FaceAlpha'` adjusts the transparency. Feel free to customize the plot further if desired.
